  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "In OpenShift, we're adding support for idling the pods managed by a `Deployment`, `ReplicationController`, etc. This would happen after e.g. we've recorded no traffic to a set of pods, and we'd set the replicas to 0. If there is an HPA associated with this, it presumably would act to increase the number of pods to the minimum value, instead of leaving it at 0 as the idler desires.\n\nWe would like to be able to indicate in some way that an HPA is temporarily disabled. I imagine this could be done via an annotation or possibly with the addition of a new field. And once the target is unidled, we'd want to reenable the HPA.\n\nThoughts anyone?\n\n@bgrant0607 @kubernetes/autoscaling @jszczepkowski @mwielgus @piosz @fgrzadkowski @kubernetes/rh-cluster-infra @smarterclayton @knobunc \n",
